There are two popular methods of inverting Eq. (122): (1) The Regularised Least Squares (RLS) method, and (2) the method of Optimally Localised Averages (OLA). These are complementary techniques (see Sekii 1997, for a discussion) that have different aims. RLS aims to find the δc2/c2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
