Solar models are constructed solving a set of coupled equations and the equation of state affects the structure in multiple ways. As a result, just looking at the sound-speed difference between models constructed with a given equation of state and the Sun does not tell us the full story. A better way is to look at the adiabatic index Γ1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
