As had been mentioned earlier in Sect. 3.3, the propagation of modes of different frequencies in star is controlled by the Lamb and Brunt–Väisälä frequencies. For a given mode, the profiles of these two frequencies determine what type of a mode it is and where it can propagate. The propagation diagram for stars in different stages of evolution can be very different from each other because of the how the Brunt–Väisälä frequency evolves with time. In Fig. 38, we show the propagation diagram for a 1M⊙\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
